rated%20at%20first%20but%20became%20violent%20after%20he%20was%20told%20he%20was%20being%20arrested%2C%20according%20to%20a%20statement%20issued%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgbi.georgia.gov%2Fpress-releases%2F2023-10-16%2Fgbi-investigates-officer-involved-shooting-camden-county%5C%22%3EGeorgia%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20spokesman%20for%20the%20Camden%20County%20Sheriff's%20Office%20told%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F17%2Fus%2Fleonard-allan-cure-georgia-deputy-shooting.html%3Fsmid%3Dfb-nytimes%26smtyp%3Dcur%26fbclid%3DIwAR1Pv-uBozxsg6cls2rv8Fs0BeXcokuf6GDDNoNAgaTNGQpdexbM5JaDlJY%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20Mr%20Cure%20was%20pulled%20over%20for%20speeding.%20He%20had%20only%20been%20out%20of%20prison%20for%20three%20and%20a%20half%20years%20following%20his%20exoneration%20when%20the%20tragic%20incident%20happened.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E''The%20driver%20of%20the%20car%2C%20later%20identified%20as%20Leonard%20Allan%20Cure%2C%20age%2053%2C%20got%20out%20of%20the%20car%20at%20the%20deputy's%20request.%20Cure%20complied%20with%20the%20officer's%20commands%20until%20he%20learned%20that%20he%20was%20under%20arrest.%20After%20not%20complying%20with%20the%20deputy's%20requests%2C%20the%20deputy%20tased%20Cure.%20Cure%20assaulted%20the%20deputy.%20The%20deputy%20used%20the%20Taser%20for%20a%20second%20time%20and%20an%20ASP%20baton%3B%20however%2C%20Cure%20still%20did%20not%20comply.%20The%20deputy%20pulled%20out%20his%20gun%20and%20shot%20Cure.%20EMT's%20treated%20Cure%2C%20but%20he%20later%20died%2C''%20the%20police%20statement%20read.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Mr%20Cure%20was%20wrongfully%20convicted%20in%202003%20of%20armed%20robbery%2C%20according%20to%20the%20criminal%20justice%20organization%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.floridainnocence.org%2Fleonard-cure%5C%22%3EInnocence%20Project.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0In%20a%20reinvestigation%20of%20the%20crime%2C%20evidence%20of%20an%20ATM%20receipt%20emerged%20proving%20that%20''Lenny%20was%20miles%20away%20from%20the%20crime%20scene%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20robbery.''%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20released%20from%20prison%20in%20Florida%20in%202020%20after%20a%20conviction%20review%20unit%20exonerated%20him.%C2%A0In%20June%2C%20he%20was%20granted%20%24817%2C000%20in%20compensation%20for%20his%20conviction%20and%20imprisonment%2C%20along%20with%20educational%20benefits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20group's%20executive%20director%2C%20Seth%20Miller%2C%20said%20he%20was%20devastated%20by%20news%20of%20the%20death.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E''I%20can%20only%20imagine%20what%20it's%20like%20to%20know%20your%20son%20is%20innocent%20and%20watch%20him%20be%20sentenced%20to%20life%20in%20prison%2C%20to%20be%20exonerated%20and%20...%20then%20be%20told%20that%20once%20he's%20been%20freed%2C%20he's%20been%20shot%20dead.%20I%20can't%20imagine%20as%20a%20parent%20what%20that%20feels%20like%2C''%20Mr%20Miller%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E'''We%20are%20so%20terribly%20sad%20to%20share%20the%20news%20that%20Leonard%20was%20shot%20and%20killed%20by%20a%20Camden%20County%20Georgia%20Sheriff's%20deputy%20during%20a%20traffic%20stop%20on%20October%2016th%2C%202023%20while%20driving%20back%20from%20Florida%20to%20his%20residence%20in%20Georgia.%C2%A0Lenny%20was%20a%20great%20person%20who%20had%20already%20lost%2016%20years%20of%20his%20life%20to%20wrongful%20incarceration.%20And%20now%20this.%20He%20and%20his%20family%20deserved%20better.%20Lenny's%20life%20mattered.%20We%20are%20completely%20devastated%2C''%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.floridainnocence.org%2Fleonard-cure%5C%22%3Ea%20statement%20on%20Innocence%20Project%20%3C%2Fa%3Eread.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697628900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-04%2Fgun-generic_650x400_71492513551.jp