ostile%20actors%20from%20intercepting%20Western%20intelligence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20American%20cybersecurity%20researcher%20exploited%20a%20glitch%20on%20the%20CIA's%20X%20account%20to%20redirect%20potential%20Russian%20informants%20to%20his%20own%20Telegram%20channel%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Ftechnology-67137773%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20BBC%20News.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20McSheehan%2C%2037%2C%20said%20he%20identified%20and%20exploited%20the%20glitch%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter%2C%20to%20prevent%20any%20hostile%20actors%20from%20capitalizing%20on%20the%20mistake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20saw%20that%20the%20official%20Telegram%20link%20they%20were%20sharing%20could%20be%20hijacked%20%E2%80%94%20and%20my%20biggest%20fear%20was%20that%20a%20country%20like%20Russia%2C%20China%2C%20or%20North%20Korea%20could%20easily%20intercept%20Western%20intelligence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BBC%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20CIA%20really%20dropped%20the%20ball%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CIA%20account%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter%2C%20displayed%20a%20link%20at%20some%20point%20after%20September%2027%20to%20a%20Telegram%20channel%20containing%20info%20about%20how%20to%20contact%20the%20organization%20through%20the%20dark%20net%20or%20other%20covert%20methods%2C%20BBC%20News%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20due%20to%20a%20flaw%20in%20how%20X%20displays%20certain%20links%2C%20the%20URL%20had%20been%20truncated%20to%20an%20unclaimed%20Telegram%20username%2C%20per%20BBC%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcSheehan%20noticed%20the%20glitch%2C%20telling%20the%20news%20outlet%3A%20%26quot%3BMy%20immediate%20thought%20was%20panic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20Insider%20that%20a%20few%20worst-case%20scenarios%20instantly%20%26quot%3Braced%20through%20my%20mind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20stop%20this%2C%20he%20registered%20the%20username%20so%20that%20anyone%20clicking%20the%20link%2C%20potentially%20to%20act%20as%20an%20informant%2C%20was%20led%20to%20his%20own%20Telegram%20channel%2C%20BBC%20News%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20featured%20a%20%26quot%3Bhigh-visibility%26quot%3B%20warning%20informing%20users%20that%20it%20was%20not%20an%20official%20CIA%20channel%20and%20urging%20them%20not%20to%20provide%20any%20secretive%20information%2C%20McSheehan%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcSheehan%20told%20BBC%20News%20that%20he%20did%20what%20he%20did%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsecurity%20precaution%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20problem%20with%20the%20X%20site%20that%20I've%20seen%20before%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20was%20amazed%20to%20see%20the%20CIA%20hadn't%20noticed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcSheehan%20told%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20multitude%20of%20attacks%20could%20have%20taken%20place%26quot%3B%20had%20he%20not%20stepped%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20needed%20to%20be%20locked%20down%20ASAP%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20commended%20the%20CIA%20for%20their%20fast%20response%20to%20fixing%20the%20issue%20after%20being%20notified%20of%20the%20glitch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CIA%2C%20which%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment%2C%20has%20since%20corrected%20the%20error.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EX%20also%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20a%20comment%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-researcher-hijacked-glitch-cia-x-account-russia-informants-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697624319000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652faaf896f7540cd05f1958%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-researcher-hijacked-glitch-cia-x-account-russia-informants-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3