t%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20describing%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esense%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.health.harvard.edu%2Fblog%2Fnumb-from-the-news-understanding-why-and-what-to-do-may-help-2021031822176%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNumbness%2520is%2520one%2520possible%2520response%2C)%2520to%2520numbness%2520(freeze).%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enumbness%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20some%20workers%20feel%20as%20more%20and%20more%20return%20to%20the%20office%20this%20fall.%20Commuting%2C%20%3Cspan%3Esifting%20through%20piles%20of%20Slack%20and%20Teams%20messages%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20and%20working%20toward%20a%20deadline%20can%20make%20mounting%20global%20crises%20seem%20far%20away%2C%20or%20even%20imagined.%20It's%20a%20harsh%20reminder%20that%20the%20early%20pandemic's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhustle-culture-got-america-addicted-to-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etemporary%20suspension%20of%20hustle%20culture%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshift%20to%20fully%20remote%20schedules%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20over%2C%20and%20many%20of%20us%20are%20back%20to%20business%20as%20usual%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20the%20world%20isn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20it's%20like%20to%20work%20through%20a%20dystopia%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20unusual%20to%20feel%20numb%20during%20hard%20times.%20The%20fight%2C%20flight%2C%20or%20freeze%20instinct%20can%20kick%20in%20during%20tough%20news%20cycles%20or%20rough%20personal%20events%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.health.harvard.edu%2Fblog%2Fnumb-from-the-news-understanding-why-and-what-to-do-may-help-2021031822176%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNumbness%2520is%2520one%2520possible%2520response%2C)%2520to%2520numbness%2520(freeze).%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHarvard%20Medical%20School%20analysis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20freeze%20instinct%20might%20appear%20as%20indifference%20on%20the%20surface%2C%20but%20it%20can%20manifest%20as%20generalized%20anxiety%2C%20or%20even%20nightmares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC9063250%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20early%20impacts%20of%20the%20Covid%20lockdown%20found%20that%20we%20were%20indeed%20remembering%20our%20dreams%20more%2C%20and%20those%20dreams%20more%20increasingly%20focused%20on%20confinement%2C%20illness%2C%20war%2C%20and%20death.%20That%20could%20contribute%20to%20a%20low-grade%2C%20generalized%20anxiety%20pumping%20through%20your%20veins%20as%20you%20sort%20a%20spreadsheet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20push%20for%20normalcy%20that's%20happening%20at%20a%20wave%20of%20companies%20right%20now%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emight%20be%20a%20brief%2C%20welcome%20reprieve%20during%20hard%20times%20for%20some%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efeel%20invalidating%20for%20some%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eworkers%2C%20says%20Dr.%20Lily%20Brown%2C%20director%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20the%20Treatment%20and%20Study%20of%20Anxiety%20in%20the%20Perelman%20School%20of%20Medicine%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20some%2C%20working%20provides%20some%20of%20the%20only%20effective%20distraction%20from%20horrible%20realities%20outside%20of%20work.%20It%20can%20be%20helpful%20when%20work%20is%20tied%20to%20a%20sense%20of%20purpose%2C%20giving%20back%20to%20the%20world%2C%20or%20if%20it%20helps%20to%20connect%20to%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Brown%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20distraction%20tends%20to%20only%20be%20helpful%20in%20the%20short-run%3B%20it%20doesn't%20allow%20individuals%20to%20process%20their%20complicated%20emotions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dichotomy%20between%20real-world%20problems%20and%20work%20obligations%20has%20also%20inspired%20Ben%20Sweeny's%20TikTok%20content.%20In%20%3Ca%20