0HC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F12163734%2Fmaxresdefault_live.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Appeals%20to%20grant%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(ST)%20status%20to%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20Meitei%20community%20have%20been%20rejected%20twice%20in%20the%20last%2040%20years%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fst-status-for-meiteis-was-considered-and-rejected-in-1982-and-2001-government-records-show%2Farticle67420818.ece%5C%22%3Edocuments%20accessed%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20was%20examined%20and%20rejected%2C%20first%2C%20in%201982%2C%20by%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20Registrar%20General%20of%20India%20(RGI)%3B%20and%20again%2C%20in%202001%2C%20by%20the%20Manipur%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Union%20and%20Manipur%20governments%20did%20not%20make%20this%20information%20public%20during%20the%20ongoing%20ethnic%20conflict%20in%20the%20state%2C%20nor%20presented%20these%20records%20in%20the%20Manipur%20high%20court%20case%20on%20the%20Meitei%20petition%20for%20inclusion%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fst-status-for-meiteis-was-considered-and-rejected-in-1982-and-2001-government-records-show%2Farticle67420818.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20tribal%20affairs%20ministry%20fished%20out%20the%20old%20documents%20just%20days%20after%20the%20Manipur%20high%20court%20order%20to%20consider%20ST%20status%20for%20Meiteis%20was%20made%20public.%20After%20the%20judgment%2C%20the%20state%20saw%20violence%20between%20the%20Meitie%20and%20the%20Kuki-Zo%20communities%2C%20which%20led%20to%20the%20death%20of%20nearly%20180%20people%20and%20engulfed%20Manipur%20in%20a%20five-month%20long%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrevious%20requests%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20records%2C%20accessed%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20under%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%2C%20showed%20that%20the%20RGI%E2%80%99s%20office%20had%20looked%20into%20the%20Meiteis%E2%80%99%20inclusion%20in%20the%20ST%20list%20on%20a%20request%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20in%201982.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20RGI%E2%80%99s%20office%20found%20that%20based%20on%20%E2%80%9Cavailable%20information%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Meitei%20community%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20appear%20to%20possess%20tribal%20characteristics%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20said%20that%20it%20was%20not%20in%20favour%20of%20inclusion.%20It%20noted%20that%20historically%2C%20the%20term%20had%20been%20used%20to%20describe%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnon-tribal%20population%20in%20the%20Manipur%20valley%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdespite-repeated-requests-pm-modi-avoids-meeting-manipur-bjp-mlas%5C%22%3EDespite%20Repeated%20Requests%2C%20PM%20Modi%20Avoids%20Meeting%20Manipur%20BJP%20MLAs%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202001%2C%20the%20erstwhile%20social%20justice%20ministry%20had%20sought%20the%20Manipur%20government%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20while%20revising%20the%20SC%2FST%20lists%20of%20states%20and%20Union%20territories.%20In%20response%2C%20the%20Tribal%20Development%20Department%20of%20Manipur%2C%20on%20January%203%2C%202001%2C%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fst-status-for-meiteis-was-considered-and-rejected-in-1982-and-2001-government-records-show%2Farticle67420818.ece%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Union%20that%20it%20agreed%20with%20the%201982%20opinion%20of%20the%20RGI%20on%20the%20status%20of%20Meiteis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThen%20chief%20minister%20of%20Manupur%2C%20W.%20Napamacha%20Singh%2C%20had%20said%20that%20the%20Meitei%20community%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdominant%20group%20in%20Manipur%E2%80%9D%20and%20need%20not%20be%20included%20in%20the%20ST%20list.%20It%20noted%20that%20Meitei%20people%20were%20Hindus%20and%20%E2%80%9Cassumed%20the%20status%20of%20Kshatriya%20Caste%20in%20the%20ladder%20of%20Hindu%20Castes%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20they%20had%20already%20been%20listed%20as%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBCs).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20documents%20were%20not%20submitted%20to%20the%20single%20judge%20bench%20of%20Acting%20Chief%20Justice%20M.V.%20Muralidharan%20who%20was%20hearing%20the%20Meiteis%E2%80%99%20petition%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20criteria%20for%20inclusion%20in%20the%20ST%20list%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20criteria%20followed%20by%20the%20RGI%20to%20determine%20whether%20a%20community%20should%20be%20included%20in%20the%20ST%20list%20were%20set%20in%201965%20and%20are%20followed%20even%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20proposal%20to%20change%20this%20criteria%2C%20based%20on%20an%20internal%20committee%E2%80%99s%20report%2C%20was%20floated%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Tribal%20Affairs%20in%202014%2C%20soon%20after%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20government%20came%20to%20power.%20In%202022%2C%20officials%20said%20there%20were%20no%20plans%20to%20change%20the%20decades-old%20criteria%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20one%20of%20the%20recommendations%20made%20by%20the%20internal%20committee%20was%20to%20not%20discount%20a%20community%E2%80%99s%20plea%20for%20inclusion%20in%20the%20ST%20list%20solely%20based%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20were%20followers%20of%20Hinduism%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697623208000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F07%2F12163734%2Fmaxresdefault_live.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Finclusion-of-meiteis-in-st-list-rejected-in-1982-2001-historical-documents-kept-from-manip